article.headline: Arizona 69, San Diego St. 56
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. -- Jordan Hill scored 25 points and Jamelle Horne had all 8 of his points down the stretch as Arizona beat San Diego State 69-56 Wednesday night. Hill, who had his seventh double-double of the season by adding 14 rebounds, had three free throws and Horne had a breakaway away dunk in the final 53 seconds to help Arizona (6-2) score the final 11 points of the game. San Diego State (7-2) didn't score the final 4:16 after D.J. Gay hit a pair of free throws to trim the Wildcats lead to 58-56. Horne was scoreless before making four free throws and a follow-up dunk to put Arizona ahead 62-56 with 3:01 remaining. Chase Budinger added 14 points for the Wildcats while Nic Wise had 13. Tim Shelton led the Aztecs with 13 points.
